  "prompt": "How can I apply for Canadian PR without hiring a consultant?",
  "response": "Here are steps to apply for Canadian Permanent Residence without a consultant:\n\n1. Determine your eligibility\n- Check immigration programs like Express Entry\n- Federal Skilled Worker\n- Provincial Nominee Program\n- Canadian Experience Class\n\n2. Required documents\n- Passport\n- Educational credentials\n- Language test results (IELTS/CELPIP)\n- Work experience proof\n- Police clearance certificate\n- Medical examination results\n\n3. Create an online profile\n- Set up account on official Canadian immigration website\n- Complete Express Entry profile\n- Include all necessary information accurately\n\n4. Calculate CRS (Comprehensive Ranking System) score\n- Use online CRS calculators\n- Understand point allocation\n- Improve score if possible\n\n5. Gather required documents\n- Get documents translated\n- Get educational credential assessment\n- Obtain work experience letters\n\n6. Submit application\n- Pay required fees\n- Upload documents electronically\n- Ensure all information is accurate\n\n7. Follow up\n- Check application status regularly\n- Respond promptly to any requests\n- Be patient during processing\n\n8. Helpful resources\n- Official Government of Canada immigration website\n- Online forums\n- Immigration discussion groups\n\nRecommended websites:\n- www.canada.ca/immigration\n- www.ircc.gc.ca",
